text: Marina Stefanoni (born 30 November 2002 in Darien, Connecticut) is an American professional squash player. Marina was the youngest National Champion in the Under 19 division in U.S. Squash history at 13 years old and ranks No. 56 in the Professional Squash Association’s World Rankings with four wins on the PSA tour as an amateur. Graduating from Darien High School in 2020, Marina attends Harvard College where she plays on the Women's Squash Team. ==References== Category:2002 births Category:Living people Category:American female squash players
